{"type":"message","id":"7c64bd21","parentId":"6c654048","timestamp":"2026-04-10T05:58:21.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to learn about Harness from GitHub and create something related to the Feishu minutes link they shared. The URL is the same Feishu minutes link. \n\nI think the user might be saying that the learning material about Harness is available on GitHub, and the Feishu link is just reference. Or maybe they want me to search GitHub for Harness-related materials and learn/create from there.\n\nLet me search GitHub for Harness-related content, specifically looking for Harness engineering or Harness framework related to AI/LLM.\n\nActually, re-reading: \"需要你再github上学习并创建 Harness\" - this likely means \"I need you to learn from GitHub and create Harness [engineering documentation]\". The Feishu link might just be context about what Harness is.\n\n\nI'll start by searching GitHub for relevant Harness repositories and information.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，去 GitHub 上找 Harness 相关的资料学习。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5n0vah1ra2s0_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"GitHub Harness engineering AI LLM framework Anthropic"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":725,"output":221,"cacheRead":43899,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44845,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775800693112,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8798d323-7e42-443a-aee6-30806d1fa952"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a58c2155","parentId":"7c64bd21","timestamp":"2026-04-10T05:58:23.717Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5n0vah1ra2s0_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"GitHub Harness engineering AI LLM framework Anthropic\",\n  \"provider\": \"miaoda\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/AgentBoardTT/openharness\",\n      \"description\": \"Code\\nCode\\n<table>\\n<tr><td>\\ntuanthi</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>.github</td><td>.github</td><td>Fix CI: use --extra dev to install dev dependencies</td><td></td></tr>\\n<tr><td>bench</td><td>bench</td><td>Initial commit: Harness multi-provider coding agent</td><td></td></tr>\\n<tr><td>docs</td...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Awesome Agent Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/AutoJunjie/awesome-agent-harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Linear Coding Agent Harness — Linear → autonomous coding agent → PR pipeline.\\nGitHub Copilot Coding Agent — Built-in GitHub issue → Copilot agent → PR.\\nAxon — Kubernetes-native framework. Apply a Task CRD, get back a PR and cost in USD. TaskSpawner watches GitHub Issues.\\nDexto — Coding agent and general agent harness for building agentic applications.\\nAgent Harness Frameworks\\nFrameworks for building custom harnesses. Following the principle that \\\"...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"celesteanders /harness-engineering-best-practices.md\",\n      \"url\": \"https://gist.github.com/celesteanders/21edad2367c8ede2ff092bd87e56a26f\",\n      \"description\": \"celeste anders / harness - engineering - best - practices . md created april 2, 2026 01 : 33 harness engineering best practices from anthropic and openai raw harness - engineering - best - practices . ...\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"anthropic\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/topics/anthropic?o=desc\",\n      \"description\": \"Aider-AI / aider\\naider is AI...\\n[Bedrock, Azure, OpenAI, VertexAI, Cohere, Anthropic, Sagemaker, HuggingFace, VLLM, NVIDIA NIM]\\ngateway bedrock openai vertex-ai azure-openai llm langchain llmops anthropic openai-proxy litellm ai-gateway llm-gateway mcp-gateway\\nUpdated Mar 17, 2026\\nPython\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Ovidiu's Claude Code Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/oeftimie/vv-claude-harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Ovidiu's Claude Code Harness\\nA harness system for Claude Code that solves multi-session continuity, parallel agent coordination, and automated quality enforcement. Built on Anthropic's research for long-running tasks, evolved through three major versions into a system that uses 100% of Claude Code's native Agent Teams primitives.\\nCurrent version: v3.2.1\\nEverything you need is in this repo:\\nDownload harness-v3.2.1.zip\\nFollow the INST...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Engineering 最佳实践:长运行多智能体的框架设计_Anthropic_童子龙_InfoQ写作社区\",\n      \"url\": \"https://xie.infoq.cn/article/664d667e256b45f92c70e0b26\",\n      \"description\": \"将这个思想迁移到 AI 编程领域：Generator 负责写代码，Evaluator 负责判断代码质量。\\n\\\"将做工作的智能体与评判工作的智能体分离，是一个强有力的杠杆\\\"——因为让评估者变得更加怀疑，远比让生成者变得更加自我批判要容易得多。 — Anthropic Engineering\\n在 Harness Engineering 中，我们将这个二元对立推广为一个六智能体流水线：\\n<代码开始>用户需求 →...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Agents\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/platform/harness-aida/harness-agents/\",\n      \"description\": \"<tr><td>BYOM — Bring Your Own Model</td> <td>Connect Anthropic, OpenAI, or Gemini via LLM Connectors. Switch models per agent, per environment, per pipeline. Use SaaS-hosted models or bring self-hosted models with a custom endpoint.</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>Knowledge Graph</td> <td>Agents query your organizational Knowledge Graph for real-time context: service topology, pipeline history, deployment state, config drift,...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"feat(agentic-engineering): harness design patterns from Anthropic research #72\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/diegouis/provectus-marketplace/pull/72/files\",\n      \"description\": \"feat ( agentic - engineering ) : harness design patterns from anthropic research # 72 diegouis merged 1 commit into main from feature / harness - design - patterns apr 6 , 2026 52 plugin ...\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Anthropic-to-OpenAI Proxy\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/zorak1103/anthropic-proxy\",\n      \"description\": \"A lightweight API proxy that translates Anthropic Messages API requests to OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions API format. This allows you to use Anthropic API clients (like Claude Code) with any OpenAI-compatible backend such as OpenRouter, local LLMs, or other providers.\\nFeatures\\nTranslates Anthropic Messages API to OpenAI Chat Completions API\\nSupports both streaming and non-streaming responses\\nFull tool/function calling translation (bidirectional)\\nHandles image content blocks...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Skills\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/walkinglabs/learn-harness-engineering/blob/main/skills/README.md\",\n      \"description\": \") to perform specialized tasks.\\nAvailable Skills\\nharness-creator\\nProduction harness engineering skill for AI coding agents. Helps create, assess, and improve agent harness files (AGENTS.md, feature lists, verification workflows, session continuity mechanisms).\\n5 reference patterns: Memory Persistence, Context Engineering, Tool Registry, Multi-Agent Coordination, Lifecycle & Bootstrap\\nTemplates: AGENTS.md, feature-list.The skill-creator provides a structured workflow (draft → test → evaluate → iterate...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"GitHub Harness engineering AI LLM framework Anthropic","provider":"miaoda","count":10,"results":[{"title":"Harness","url":"https://github.com/AgentBoardTT/openharness","description":"Code\nCode\n<table>\n<tr><td>\ntuanthi</td></tr>\n<tr><td>.github</td><td>.github</td><td>Fix CI: use --extra dev to install dev dependencies</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>bench</td><td>bench</td><td>Initial commit: Harness multi-provider coding agent</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td>docs</td...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Awesome Agent Harness","url":"https://github.com/AutoJunjie/awesome-agent-harness","description":"Linear Coding Agent Harness — Linear → autonomous coding agent → PR pipeline.\nGitHub Copilot Coding Agent — Built-in GitHub issue → Copilot agent → PR.\nAxon — Kubernetes-native framework. Apply a Task CRD, get back a PR and cost in USD. TaskSpawner watches GitHub Issues.\nDexto — Coding agent and general agent harness for building agentic applications.\nAgent Harness Frameworks\nFrameworks for building custom harnesses. Following the principle that \"...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"celesteanders /harness-engineering-best-practices.md","url":"https://gist.github.com/celesteanders/21edad2367c8ede2ff092bd87e56a26f","description":"celeste anders / harness - engineering - best - practices . md created april 2, 2026 01 : 33 harness engineering best practices from anthropic and openai raw harness - engineering - best - practices . ...","siteName":""},{"title":"anthropic","url":"https://github.com/topics/anthropic?o=desc","description":"Aider-AI / aider\naider is AI...\n[Bedrock, Azure, OpenAI, VertexAI, Cohere, Anthropic, Sagemaker, HuggingFace, VLLM, NVIDIA NIM]\ngateway bedrock openai vertex-ai azure-openai llm langchain llmops anthropic openai-proxy litellm ai-gateway llm-gateway mcp-gateway\nUpdated Mar 17, 2026\nPython","siteName":""},{"title":"Ovidiu's Claude Code Harness","url":"https://github.com/oeftimie/vv-claude-harness","description":"Ovidiu's Claude Code Harness\nA harness system for Claude Code that solves multi-session continuity, parallel agent coordination, and automated quality enforcement. Built on Anthropic's research for long-running tasks, evolved through three major versions into a system that uses 100% of Claude Code's native Agent Teams primitives.\nCurrent version: v3.2.1\nEverything you need is in this repo:\nDownload harness-v3.2.1.zip\nFollow the INST...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Engineering 最佳实践:长运行多智能体的框架设计_Anthropic_童子龙_InfoQ写作社区","url":"https://xie.infoq.cn/article/664d667e256b45f92c70e0b26","description":"将这个思想迁移到 AI 编程领域：Generator 负责写代码，Evaluator 负责判断代码质量。\n\"将做工作的智能体与评判工作的智能体分离，是一个强有力的杠杆\"——因为让评估者变得更加怀疑，远比让生成者变得更加自我批判要容易得多。 — Anthropic Engineering\n在 Harness Engineering 中，我们将这个二元对立推广为一个六智能体流水线：\n<代码开始>用户需求 →...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Agents","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/platform/harness-aida/harness-agents/","description":"<tr><td>BYOM — Bring Your Own Model</td> <td>Connect Anthropic, OpenAI, or Gemini via LLM Connectors. Switch models per agent, per environment, per pipeline. Use SaaS-hosted models or bring self-hosted models with a custom endpoint.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Knowledge Graph</td> <td>Agents query your organizational Knowledge Graph for real-time context: service topology, pipeline history, deployment state, config drift,...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"feat(agentic-engineering): harness design patterns from Anthropic research #72","url":"https://github.com/diegouis/provectus-marketplace/pull/72/files","description":"feat ( agentic - engineering ) : harness design patterns from anthropic research # 72 diegouis merged 1 commit into main from feature / harness - design - patterns apr 6 , 2026 52 plugin ...","siteName":""},{"title":"Anthropic-to-OpenAI Proxy","url":"https://github.com/zorak1103/anthropic-proxy","description":"A lightweight API proxy that translates Anthropic Messages API requests to OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions API format. This allows you to use Anthropic API clients (like Claude Code) with any OpenAI-compatible backend such as OpenRouter, local LLMs, or other providers.\nFeatures\nTranslates Anthropic Messages API to OpenAI Chat Completions API\nSupports both streaming and non-streaming responses\nFull tool/function calling translation (bidirectional)\nHandles image content blocks...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Skills","url":"https://github.com/walkinglabs/learn-harness-engineering/blob/main/skills/README.md","description":") to perform specialized tasks.\nAvailable Skills\nharness-creator\nProduction harness engineering skill for AI coding agents. Helps create, assess, and improve agent harness files (AGENTS.md, feature lists, verification workflows, session continuity mechanisms).\n5 reference patterns: Memory Persistence, Context Engineering, Tool Registry, Multi-Agent Coordination, Lifecycle & Bootstrap\nTemplates: AGENTS.md, feature-list.The skill-creator provides a structured workflow (draft → test → evaluate → iterate...\n","siteName":""}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775800703715}}
